        <methods>
            <methodStep>
                <description>
                    <para>The vegetation-plot records were obtained from published literature, field notebooks, and existing datasets. All records were assembled in the Turboveg 2 database management software and exported to GBIF following the procedures described at https://czechveg.github.io/DataProcessingTutorial/data_processing_tutorial.html.</para>
                </description>
            </methodStep>
            <methodStep>
                <description>
                    <para>WARNING: Given that the dwc:occurrenceID is based on an attribute of the record iselft (species identification), note that re-identifications (if any) in future updates would result in new OccurrenceIDs, which would brake the link with previous identifation.</para>
                </description>
            </methodStep>
            <sampling>
                <studyExtent>
                    <description>
                        <para>The territory of the Czech Republic.</para>
                    </description>
                </studyExtent>
                <samplingDescription>
                    <para>Data in this dataset were collected in vegetation plots, most of which were 1 to 1000 square meters in size. Vascular plants were recorded in each plot if they occurred there. Additionally, bryophytes, lichens, and charophytes were recorded in some plots. The cover of each species was estimated in the field as an abundance measure.</para>
                </samplingDescription>
            </sampling>
            <qualityControl>
                <description>
                    <para>Data were checked by multiple experts in Czech flora.</para>
                </description>
            </qualityControl>
        </methods>

